Dear Dr. Goodwin,

Hello, this is Steven DeCaluwe, at the University of Maryland.  I am
trying to model charge-transfer reactions at the TPB in an
anode-supported SOFC.  However, after reading the pdf on creating cti
files, I am having trouble entering code for these reactions that
cantera/python is able to translate.  For example, here is one
reaction I have attempted to enter:


#  Reaction 0004
charge_transfer_reaction( "H_c(S) + OH_e(S) = NI(S) + H2O_e(S) +
e_Ni",
		[5e15, 0, (90, 'kJ/mol')]
	)

Are there other parameters that need to be entered?  As I remember,
the Beta value is optional, with a default of 0.5.  I also remember
you mentioning that the potentials of the different phases can be
specified; does this need to be done in the cti file, or can it be
done through the matlab interface?  (I hope it is the latter).  

Anyway, if I simply change the reaction type to "surface_reaction,"
my xml is created just fine, but obviously, these rates wouldn't
accurately represent the kinetics I am attempting to simulate.

Many thanks,
Steven DeCaluwe
